{
  "name": "xcloud-docker-deploy",
  "displayName": "xCloud Docker Deploy",
  "version": "1.4.1",
  "description": "xCloud Docker Deploy v1.4.1 — a confirmation-gated skill for preparing projects for xCloud. It can inspect a project only after user consent, recommend native or Docker deployment, generate Docker/GHCR files, fix xCloud port rules, and route live API work only after a separate explicit token-consent step.",
  "longDescription": "A human-friendly deployment assistant for xCloud hosting. Users can say: This is my project, I want to deploy it on xCloud. The agent must first confirm whether the user wants read-only analysis, file generation, or live xCloud API actions. After confirmation, the skill detects the project stack, routes to xCloud Native or Custom Docker, generates Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, GHCR GitHub Actions workflow, and .env.example, enforces xCloud-safe port mappings like 80:80 to 3080:80, and can pair with official xCloud API skills only after a separate explicit consent step for the exact live operation and token handling.",
